		A home that's no fixer-upper
		USC students will start construction this month on a model house as part of the Department of Energy's Solar Decathlon competition. Their goal: affordable and environmentally friendly housing for the future.
	
	
  
  
    Back to the beginning




You and your PC: Never ever getting back together?
A quarter of PC users report they'll ditch their computers when their current boxes become unusable, according to a survey by USC Annenberg's Center for the Digital Future and market research firm Bovitz Inc. It's not that tablets and handheld devices are more hip; their mobility seems to be a key selling point.  
Read the full story at USC News



The online learning bounty multiplies
As demand for online learning grows, USC extends its academic leadership digitally. Now spanning over nine schools, online learning in graduate-level programs at 
USC marked tremendous growth in 2012. The number of students working on degrees online, currently 4,800, is expected to increase. 
Learn more



A new hip brings new hope
Imagine arthritis so debilitating you can't walk. Practically immobile, Steve McKellar couldn't work. That meant no insurance, so he couldn't afford to replace his degenerated hip. Enter Keck School of Medicine of USC surgeon Lawrence Dorr and the charity Operation Walk USA. With their help, McKellar is on his feet again.
Read the full story at USC News



